56.6	Sodium_hydroxide	Sodium hydroxide	Sodium hydroxide , also known as lye and caustic soda, is a caustic metallic base. It is used in many industries, mostly as a strong chemical base in the manufacture of pulp and paper, textiles, drinking water, soaps and detergents and as a drain cleaner. Worldwide production in 2004 was approximately 60 million tonnes, while demand was 51 million tonnes.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/Sodium-hydroxide-crystal-3D-vdW.png/200px-Sodium-hydroxide-crystal-3D-vdW.png
